	<div class="story-detail">
									<div class="story-top">
					<span class="kicker">Special Project</span>
				</div>
						<h3 class="story-headline">
				<span class="story-link">Reparations debate: Mending the past, forging the future</span>
			</h3>
		
													<p class="story-summary">What does it mean for a society to atone for systemic and enduring harms? California is the first U.S. state to propose reparations for many Black residents. Communities across the country are watching closely. But questions of restoration and reconciliation aren’t exclusive to Black Americans – or to the United States. This special series explores efforts around the world to seek justice and restitution for communities subjected to historical harms.</p>
						</div>
	</a>
</div>
